{"type":"message","id":"0d39570f","parentId":"6b2a0c6a","timestamp":"2026-03-27T19:22:04.170Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Perfecto, entonces mejor todavía: **sí usamos Notion**.\n\nEntonces la regla queda así:\n\n- **pendientes importantes tuyos → Notion**\n- **memoria diaria → apoyo interno**\n- **memoria larga → solo lo estratégico/permanente**\n- pero la **vista operativa visible** para ti va en **Notion**\n\nEso sí tiene más sentido porque:\n- lo ves fácil\n- queda centralizado\n- otras sesiones lo pueden usar mejor\n- y no depende de que yo “me acuerde” solo por contexto local\n\n**Entonces, a partir de ahora:**\ncuando me pases tareas/pedidos importantes, lo correcto será:\n1. guardarlo en **Notion**\n2. si hace falta, dejar una nota breve en memoria\n3. usar Notion como fuente visible/operativa\n\n**Para lo de hoy**, yo metería en Notion:\n- investigar correo con dominio y costos\n- mejorar autonomía/interacción/productividad entre agentes\n- factura mensual al proveedor\n- pendiente de plantilla/template\n- futura automatización de recordatorio antes de fin de mes\n- reglas de cálculo:\n  - horario Colombia\n  - lunes a viernes\n  - festivos colombianos no\n  - 8 horas\n  - tarifa aprox. $38/hora\n\nSi quieres, en el siguiente paso te lo organizo con una estructura limpia tipo:\n- **Inbox**\n- **Next**\n- **Waiting**\n- **Recurring**\n\nY ahí dejamos esto bien puesto.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b5379d175373a9a0169c6d8d9ef888191aaff445e6038e27d\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":118,"output":314,"cacheRead":135424,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":135856,"cost":{"input":0.000295,"output":0.00471,"cacheRead":0.033856,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.038861}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774639316688,"responseId":"resp_0b5379d175373a9a0169c6d8d91fbc81919062926e3eb11a58"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ebfd29b5","parentId":"0d39570f","timestamp":"2026-03-27T19:22:33.630Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"3A9447761181CE5544B9\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"+573183718246\",\n  \"sender\": \"Gustavo Toledo\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Gustavo Toledo (+573183718246)\",\n  \"id\": \"+573183718246\",\n  \"name\": \"Gustavo Toledo\",\n  \"e164\": \"+573183718246\"\n}\n```\n\nDale guarda"}],"timestamp":1774639353626}}
{"type":"message","id":"d2e05e90","parentId":"ebfd29b5","timestamp":"2026-03-27T19:22:39.908Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Voy a leer la skill de Google Workspace/Notion y luego guardo esos pendientes en tu sistema operativo de Notion.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b5379d175373a9a0169c6d9002ce08191bfe6608afb2b8506\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_QXFwZJahOkz7Yt555bJInUJW|fc_0b5379d175373a9a0169c6d900e5848191997e3570b3fb7843","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\skills\\gog\\SKILL.md"},"partialJson":"{\"file_path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\Gustavo\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\gog\\\\SKILL.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":297,"output":80,"cacheRead":135680,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":136057,"cost":{"input":0.0007425000000000001,"output":0.0012000000000000001,"cacheRead":0.03392,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0358625}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774639353630,"responseId":"resp_0b5379d175373a9a0169c6d8fe0c708191bc008dabdbb07261"}}
{"type":"message","id":"53b091a3","parentId":"d2e05e90","timestamp":"2026-03-27T19:22:39.919Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_QXFwZJahOkz7Yt555bJInUJW|fc_0b5379d175373a9a0169c6d900e5848191997e3570b3fb7843","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: gog\ndescription: Google Workspace CLI for Gmail, Calendar, Drive, Contacts, Sheets, and Docs.\nhomepage: https://gogcli.sh\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\":\n      {\n        \"emoji\": \"🎮\",\n        \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"gog\"] },\n        \"install\":\n          [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"brew\",\n              \"kind\": \"brew\",\n              \"formula\": \"steipete/tap/gogcli\",\n              \"bins\": [\"gog\"],\n              \"label\": \"Install gog (brew)\",\n            },\n          ],\n      },\n  }\n---\n\n# gog\n\nUse `gog` for Gmail/Calendar/Drive/Contacts/Sheets/Docs. Requires OAuth setup.\n\nSetup (once)\n\n- `gog auth credentials /path/to/client_secret.json`\n- `gog auth add you@gmail.com --services gmail,calendar,drive,contacts,docs,sheets`\n- `gog auth list`\n\nCommon commands\n\n- Gmail search: `gog gmail search 'newer_than:7d' --max 10`\n- Gmail messages search (per email, ignores threading): `gog gmail messages search \"in:inbox from:ryanair.com\" --max 20 --account you@example.com`\n- Gmail send (plain): `gog gmail send --to a@b.com --subject \"Hi\" --body \"Hello\"`\n- Gmail send (multi-line): `gog gmail send --to a@b.com --subject \"Hi\" --body-file ./message.txt`\n- Gmail send (stdin): `gog gmail send --to a@b.com --subject \"Hi\" --body-file -`\n- Gmail send (HTML): `gog gmail send --to a@b.com --subject \"Hi\" --body-html \"<p>Hello</p>\"`\n- Gmail draft: `gog gmail drafts create --to a@b.com --subject \"Hi\" --body-file ./message.txt`\n- Gmail send draft: `gog gmail drafts send <draftId>`\n- Gmail reply: `gog gmail send --to a@b.com --subject \"Re: Hi\" --body \"Reply\" --reply-to-message-id <msgId>`\n- Calendar list events: `gog calendar events <calendarId> --from <iso> --to <iso>`\n- Calendar create event: `gog calendar create <calendarId> --summary \"Title\" --from <iso> --to <iso>`\n- Calendar create with color: `gog calendar create <calendarId> --summary \"Title\" --from <iso> --to <iso> --event-color 7`\n- Calendar update event: `gog calendar update <calendarId> <eventId> --summary \"New Title\" --event-color 4`\n- Calendar show colors: `gog calendar colors`\n- Drive search: `gog drive search \"query\" --max 10`\n- Contacts: `gog contacts list --max 20`\n- Sheets get: `gog sheets get <sheetId> \"Tab!A1:D10\" --json`\n- Sheets update: `gog sheets update <sheetId> \"Tab!A1:B2\" --values-json '[[\"A\",\"B\"],[\"1\",\"2\"]]' --input USER_ENTERED`\n- Sheets append: `gog sheets append <sheetId> \"Tab!A:C\" --values-json '[[\"x\",\"y\",\"z\"]]' --insert INSERT_ROWS`\n- Sheets clear: `gog sheets clear <sheetId> \"Tab!A2:Z\"`\n- Sheets metadata: `gog sheets metadata <sheetId> --json`\n- Docs export: `gog docs export <docId> --format txt --out /tmp/doc.txt`\n- Docs cat: `gog docs cat <docId>`\n\nCalendar Colors\n\n- Use `gog calendar colors` to see all available event colors (IDs 1-11)\n- Add colors to events with `--event-color <id>` flag\n- Event color IDs (from `gog calendar colors` output):\n  - 1: #a4bdfc\n  - 2: #7ae7bf\n  - 3: #dbadff\n  - 4: #ff887c\n  - 5: #fbd75b\n  - 6: #ffb878\n  - 7: #46d6db\n  - 8: #e1e1e1\n  - 9: #5484ed\n  - 10: #51b749\n  - 11: #dc2127\n\nEmail Formatting\n\n- Prefer plain text. Use `--body-file` for multi-paragraph messages (or `--body-file -` for stdin).\n- Same `--body-file` pattern works for drafts and replies.\n- `--body` does not unescape `\\n`. If you need inline newlines, use a heredoc or `$'Line 1\\n\\nLine 2'`.\n- Use `--body-html` only when you need rich formatting.\n- HTML tags: `<p>` for paragraphs, `<br>` for line breaks, `<strong>` for bold, `<em>` for italic, `<a href=\"url\">` for links, `<ul>`/`<li>` for lists.\n- Example (plain text via stdin):\n\n  ```bash\n  gog gmail send --to recipient@example.com \\\n    --subject \"Meeting Follow-up\" \\\n    --body-file - <<'EOF'\n  Hi Name,\n\n  Thanks for meeting today. Next steps:\n  - Item one\n  - Item two\n\n  Best regards,\n  Your Name\n  EOF\n  ```\n\n- Example (HTML list):\n  ```bash\n  gog gmail send --to recipient@example.com \\\n    --subject \"Meeting Follow-up\" \\\n    --body-html \"<p>Hi Name,</p><p>Thanks for meeting today. Here are the next steps:</p><ul><li>Item one</li><li>Item two</li></ul><p>Best regards,<br>Your Name</p>\"\n  ```\n\nNotes\n\n- Set `GOG_ACCOUNT=you@gmail.com` to avoid repeating `--account`.\n- For scripting, prefer `--json` plus `--no-input`.\n- Sheets values can be passed via `--values-json` (recommended) or as inline rows.\n- Docs supports export/cat/copy. In-place edits require a Docs API client (not in gog).\n- Confirm before sending mail or creating events.\n- `gog gmail search` returns one row per thread; use `gog gmail messages search` when you need every individual email returned separately.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774639359915}}
{"type":"message","id":"242eccbb","parentId":"53b091a3","timestamp":"2026-03-27T19:22:52.779Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Voy a cargar esos pendientes en Notion usando la base Tasks Tracker limpia de Atlas OS - Home.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b5379d175373a9a0169c6d9078a448191a6e2d070302d872c\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_oWX7yvsCSLIlcxOMRE8bD8t2|fc_0b5379d175373a9a0169c6d90817788191b3f996831462e10f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$headers = @{ 'Authorization' = \"Bearer $env:NOTION_TOKEN\"; 'Notion-Version' = '2022-06-28'; 'Content-Type' = 'application/json' }\n$body = @{\n  parent = @{ database_id = '32f0a0b1-97cc-81a8-9443-df3f85f2ffc7' }\n  properties = @{\n    'Task name' = @{ title = @(@{ text = @{ content = 'Investigar correo con dominio gestionado en Cloudflare (costos y opciones)' } }) }\n    'Status' = @{ status = @{ name = 'Backlog' } }\n    'Priority' = @{ select = @{ name = 'Medium' } }\n    'Owner' = @{ rich_text = @(@{ text = @{ content = 'Atlas' } }) }\n    'Area' = @{ select = @{ name = 'Operación' } }\n    'Notes' = @{ rich_text = @(@{ text = @{ content = 'Investigación únicamente por ahora. Aclarar costo si es solo reenvío vs inbox completo con proveedor externo.' } }) }\n    'Source' = @{ rich_text = @(@{ text = @{ content = 'WhatsApp Gustavo 2026-03-27' } }) }\n  }\n} | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 10\nInvoke-RestMethod -Method Post -Uri 'https://api.notion.com/v1/pages' -Headers $headers -Body $body","workdir":"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":12000,"timeout":40},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"$headers = @{ 'Authorization' = \\\"Bearer $env:NOTION_TOKEN\\\"; 'Notion-Version' = '2022-06-28'; 'Content-Type' = 'application/json' }\\n$body = @{\\n  parent = @{ database_id = '32f0a0b1-97cc-81a8-9443-df3f85f2ffc7' }\\n  properties = @{\\n    'Task name' = @{ title = @(@{ text = @{ content = 'Investigar correo con dominio gestionado en Cloudflare (costos